What I'm try to do:

```python
import gql
gql('''
mutation {
  update_document(_set: {checksum: null}, where: {checksum: {_is_null: false}}) {
    returning {
      id
    }
  }
}''')
```

That's a correct mutation that works in hasura UI (which is built on graphiql)
And it works in graphql-dotnet.

I found that similar problem was in apollo-graphql:  https://github.com/apollographql/graphql-tag/issues/47
And it was solved with graphql-tag@1.3.0

I suppose that's a bug

